<br>
As far as nukes are concerned, downtime is factored in just about equally for a wizard as for a magician.  Actually, a wizard might find himself able to meditate more, as a magician will often need to stand up to control his pet or avoid aggro.<br>
<br>
As far as the pet is concerned, he averages 5.8 damage for every second that there is a mob there to hit.  Sometimes it's a lot more, somtiems it's a lot less.  The pet hits for as hard as 28 damage per hit, but sometimes he misses completely.<br>
<br>
The point of this is to show how little damage the pet is actually doing during this time when the wizard is supposedly useless.  In many cases, a wizard sitting down has already outdamaged the magician and the pet is playing catch up.<br>
<br>
In higher uptime groups, it's true that a magician and pet will deal more damage than a wizard.  This is how it's supposed to be, it is a natural relationship between melee damage and mana based damage.  However, the point at which a magician starts to outdamage a wizard(amount of uptime) is not fixed, and in many people's opinion that number is too low.<br>
<br>
Don't overestimate the power of a pet relative to your nukes unless you just don't want to get groups<br>
