mages need +1-4 levels on 50+ pets, and +1-8 hp damage on their melee post 50,a nd a nuke that hits armour class or dodge skill. (sorry fed the HELL up with resists, whats' so damn wrong with the idea of conjuring up an object, a bolt, a meteor, hell an avil :&gt; and dropping it on a mob?)<br>
<br>
As another point, masters of DD, so why don't wizard's get &quot;anti-resist skills&quot;?, say -5 resists per 10 levels?<br>
mage antisummoned spells should either be lures, un-resistable or MUCH better efficiency. Currently they are so so.<br>
I use them in the Hole because I am sick to death, at lvl 60, of seeing resists from light/low blues on fire and magic nukes *sigh*<br>
<br>
Redorious<br>
Archmage<br>
karana<br>
