Basically the anti-summon spells probably seemed like a good idea at the time but are so rarely useful (and Mages get them so late) that they are just an oddity. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br>  Posts: 1603<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/8/02 10:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages.... &lt;glare&gt;</span><hr size=1> Sorry, I was unclear.  I meant faster damage, not just faster cast time.  A level 34 wizard chaining Shock of Frost will get a lot more spells off than a magician using blaze, but the magician will outdamage him hands down.<br>
<br>
Also, I'm not a little confused about how you came up with .12 as your average, it looks to me as if you counted the levels where magicians got no nuke at all as a difference of 0.  Which leads me back to the level one shock comparison.<br>
<br>
I also may have been a bit careless with my use of the word &quot;significantly.&quot;  I consider nuking slow enough such that my pet is required to break even with a wizard significant.  I don't believe wizards should be outdamaging a magician+pet in the short term by much, if at all.. though who is ultimately more effective is highly dependant on the situation and skill of the player(which is as it should be, imo).<br>
<br>
I think what it boils down to, is that wizards had, pre focus items anyway, some issues with long term damage in experience groups.  I think the problem in long term damage isn't as big as people try to make it sound, however, and problems in short term damage are certianly not significant relative to magicians, who are also &quot;fast burn&quot; damage specialsts just as wizards are. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilverbladetheenchanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silverblade the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 321<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/9/02 6:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: anti summons</span><hr size=1> Grim,<br>
