</center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A> at: 4/9/02 3:31:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufynalwiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fynalwiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 617<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 6:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages.... &lt;glare&gt;</span><hr size=1> Goladus,<br>
<br>
If mages and wizards are both fast burn classes, and mages do more long-term, I don't really see much point to adding a wizard to a group. <br>
<br>
First off, the very point of fast burn, has been pretty much broken down. As Grim mentioned, you need 4-5 casts to even see a difference in fast casting. If you chain-nuke like that, 1 of 2 things (or both things) will likely happen. You will get aggro and get pounded on, and/or you will be OOM really quick.<br>
<br>
Wizards are a nuking classs, it is all we have to do damage with. If we are not, and I actually believe this, the most damaging class in the game, then thier really is little argument for taking us over another class that does MORE damage but also has defensive skills. <br>
<br>
Mages have a pet. Warriors, rogues, rangers and monks all have more AC and skills, if needed, to avoid aggro. More than any other offensice class, the wizard totally and completely sacrifices defense. The reward for that should be terrifying, and unparralled. <br>
<br>
But it isnt, furthermore there are many who apparently think it should be. If we are to keep finishing somewhere in the middle of the pack of damage dealers, there is simply no argument for this class to exist, except as TLers.<br>
<br>
Fast-burn, as a concept, is situational and certainly not needed in a group. If you plan to take away even that, then you remove the final, though creaky, argument for even having a wizard around.<br>
<br>
Fynal <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=698.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=698.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=698.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=698.topic&start=81&stop=82>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=698.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=698.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=698.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=698.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=698.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=698.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email n